Map Name: fy_dev_hexakilla Players: 8-12 Buy zone: Yes, at highest point in map. Flow: Very good, several ways to choke points flanking maneuvers execute quickly and efficiently. slight advantage to CT, as the path to T spawn is more easily maneuvered. In return the road from T to CT spawn is more covered and defensive. Eye Candy: Nil, i did raise the light map scale to give it some extra. There are lit textures instead of light entities. the hex pits add extra challenge and there are a few jump obstacles that help the game play for sure. This map is full of 'Z' axis game play, plenty of routes, and it damn near feels flow-a-matic. Greyfrogs Hexagon Series

Well, I decided that the first version of this map was successful and fun enough to be worth making a more serious effort at a better version. The size of the inside of the map is actually the size I had had the original version in my mind. I added quite a lot more things too though, including roof access for terrorists and an entirely remade from scratch layout. It does bear resembelence to the original map though.

This version of the map works nearly as well with bots as the original version, but they are once again quite suicidal. I did fix the CTs going round in circles jumping off one of the platforms though. It also supports many more bots/players due to the increase in size and complexity of the map. It can probably even handle more players than the recommended amount(24).

Another noteworthy feature of the map is HDR. I decided to add this because I noticed that the map was a small file size so it would be feasible for people to download it off servers even with HDR.

UPDATE: version 2.5 adds some ladders to the outside to keep the action more focused at the bottom of the tower, as well as adding another walkway inside the tower.
Used dev textures. used the grey/orange blend texture for once.

This is a map that I had an idea of quite a while ago. The basic idea is that the terrorists start at the top of the map and the CTs at the bottom. in the tower there are lots of walkways, ramps and ladders that the players can use to reach the top of the tower.

To be honest, I could have spent longer on this but I just wanted to evaluate the gameplay potential of the idea. In that sense, I think it has turned out well. The map is also good to use with bots, but they can be a bit suicidal from fall damage.

-----
Ok so finished this map today and it's now time to add it here :)
-----
This is pretty decent fy map imo. Should be optimal for around 10 players. I used time with rounded corners and such for better look and detail. And now to the biggest point of the map.
EVERY WOODEN PART IN THE MAP CAN BE DESTROYED!!
 Yeah that's right. Every part with wooden texture can be shot down. Just look at the screenshots, there's alot things you can destroy! That's why I named it destructible ;)
-----
I didn't have really time for good bug testing, so I'd highly apreciate if you could tell me if you're going to put this on your servers, because I'd like to take a look how it works with much players. Also, please post a comment if you find any bugs or exploits so I can fix them for beta 2 :)

-32 player spawns (16 each team) -3D Skybox -Lots of func_breakable entitys -Dark lighting with lots of shadows -Huge amount of decals -Nav -file -And epic sexiness by SwatMat ;)

Toast

This is the first map I ever actually completed that wasn't just one side versus another. I made this one a couple years back, hence the too short doors and general lack of detail. I have given up on it totally, having moved on to other, better looking projects.

The map itself has multiple paths for both teams to take. Both teams have access to a joined vent that leads up to a rooftop, bot have a corridor that leads to the center, CT has ladder access to the rooftops, and T has easy access to the sewers. The sewers link to the basement which has two other exits to the surface. There is also a couple hidden rooms in this map, but I'll let you guys find those yourselves. ;P

Anyways, have fun with it. I did, even against bots.
